WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.960
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, a great constitutional question which I have

00:10.960 --> 00:15.820
previously discussed with you was in the forefront of consideration here in the Senate

00:15.820 --> 00:17.760
again this week.

00:17.760 --> 00:23.520
This question concerns what we as a nation can do in order to assure firm leadership.

00:23.520 --> 00:28.520
Should there be some future occasion when the President is not able to act?

00:28.520 --> 00:32.120
The Constitution itself is not clear on this subject.

00:32.120 --> 00:36.480
It says that in the event of the inability of the President to discharge the powers and

00:36.480 --> 00:42.760
duties of his office, and I have the Constitution here, the same shall the bar on the vice

00:42.760 --> 00:48.480
president, and the Congress may by law provide for the case of removal, death, resignation,

00:48.480 --> 00:52.240
or inability both of the President and the vice president.

00:52.240 --> 00:57.600
Declaring what office should then act as President, and such office should act accordingly

00:57.600 --> 01:02.880
until the disability be removed, our President shall be elected.

01:02.880 --> 01:07.240
Now you will see that the Constitution seems to talk of an acting President.

01:07.240 --> 01:10.680
We have as a matter of fact never had an acting President.

01:10.680 --> 01:14.960
Due to the President established by vice president John Talon.

01:14.960 --> 01:19.800
When he assumed the office of the President, see in 1841, after the death of President

01:19.800 --> 01:27.360
Harrison, he took the oath of office as President and contended that he was in fact the President.

01:27.360 --> 01:31.960
This President has been confirmed six times by every vice president who succeeded to the

01:31.960 --> 01:37.920
office at the death of a President, namely Phil Moore and Drew Johnson, author, Theodore

01:37.920 --> 01:41.320
Roosevelt, Coolidge, and Harry Truman.

01:41.320 --> 01:46.280
The fact that the President has been so firmly established that a vice president assumes

01:46.280 --> 01:52.480
the office of President, rather than the powers and duties of the office, has served to inject

01:52.480 --> 01:58.000
a great deal of doubt about what if anything can be done while a President is temporarily

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
disabled to do anything.

02:00.000 --> 02:06.600
In 1881, for example, during the 80 days of President Garfield's fatal illness, he performed

02:06.600 --> 02:10.640
but one single act, the signing of an extradition paper.

02:10.640 --> 02:15.200
The cabinet discussed what should be done, and although all agreed that it would be well

02:15.200 --> 02:20.040
for Vice President, author to act as President, a majority of them felt that he could not do

02:20.040 --> 02:23.960
so temporarily, so they decided to do nothing.

02:23.960 --> 02:29.400
And President Woodrow Wilson was ill almost the entire last two and a half years of his

02:29.400 --> 02:31.000
second turn.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.640
During this period, as all of you know, leaders of the Senate were refused permission to

02:34.640 --> 02:38.960
even see him to discuss the treaty of their side.

02:38.960 --> 02:43.840
The affairs of government were largely disposed of by decisions of the President's wife, his

02:43.840 --> 02:48.320
decision in the White House and certain members of the cabinet.

02:48.320 --> 02:50.600
The League of Nations was lost.

02:50.600 --> 02:54.200
28 acts became law without his signature.

02:54.200 --> 02:58.720
In more recent days, we have all known the concern occasioned by President Eisenhower

02:58.720 --> 03:02.840
when he had a heart attack and with his subsequent illnesses.

03:02.840 --> 03:07.640
And as a matter of fact, President Eisenhower has himself urged that something be done about

03:07.640 --> 03:08.960
this problem of disability.

03:08.960 --> 03:13.920
Thus, we have had plenty of warnings, and we have known for a long time that this is

03:13.920 --> 03:16.520
a problem that should be solved.

03:16.520 --> 03:21.880
In today's fast-moving world of satellites, missiles, and jets, and atomic power, we

03:21.880 --> 03:27.840
might someday find ourselves helpless as a nation in a crucial period unless we do solve.

03:27.840 --> 03:31.760
Whenever an attempt has been made toward a solution in the past, we have found ourselves

03:31.760 --> 03:36.240
arguing over the tales and eventually neglecting the problems.

03:36.240 --> 03:40.760
This year's Chairman of the Constitutional Amendment Subcommittee, I have conducted hearings

03:40.760 --> 03:43.000
on proposed solutions.

03:43.000 --> 03:48.000
This week, a bipartisan group of us, including a majority of the members of the Subcommittee

03:48.000 --> 03:54.440
and of the full Judiciary Committee, introduced a joint resolution which I think is a satisfactory

03:54.440 --> 03:55.440
solution.

03:55.440 --> 04:00.920
I have the resolution here and is post-sponsored by quite a number of the leaders of the Judiciary

04:00.920 --> 04:02.720
Committee in the Senate.

04:02.720 --> 04:07.760
It is a constitutional amendment, providing the means by which the Vice President and

04:07.760 --> 04:12.960
temporarily assume the powers and duties of the office, and by which they can be reassigned

04:12.960 --> 04:16.320
and assumed in the event of a President's recovery.

04:16.320 --> 04:21.280
And should there be disagreement between the Vice President and the President as to his

04:21.280 --> 04:26.400
recovery, Congress by two-thirds vote would solve the question?

04:26.400 --> 04:29.400
This proposal was immediately endorsed by President Eisenhower.

04:29.400 --> 04:35.200
And I am hopeful that we can start the constitutional amendment on its ways so it may be acted

04:35.200 --> 04:38.320
upon by the legislators of the various states this year.

04:38.320 --> 04:41.000
It is very important that we do so.

04:41.240 --> 04:43.240
Thank you and goodbye until next week.

