As he's the representative of the executive end of NATO's photospeed.

11:35.680 --> 11:40.080
We talked with him first about the proposed citizens conference.

11:40.080 --> 11:46.620
This would be a relatively small group, 50 or 60, citizens from all of the NATO nations

11:46.620 --> 11:52.440
who would study and meet and meet together as long as necessary to find out the reasons

11:52.440 --> 11:59.840
for the things that divide us and recommend ways and means of solving these problems.

11:59.840 --> 12:06.080
This is back promised to present this proposal to the next council meeting of NATO in April.

12:06.080 --> 12:10.640
If enough member government show that they want it, then I think this step, which I believe

12:10.640 --> 12:15.720
to be of great and overriding importance, may be a fact she is.

12:15.720 --> 12:22.600
We then talked to Mr. Spack about the congress meeting in 1959, and he promised also to present

12:22.600 --> 12:26.120
that proposal to the next council meeting.

12:26.120 --> 12:32.280
This proposed congress would be modeled along the lines of the Hague Conference of 1948,

12:32.280 --> 12:36.160
which was inspired by that great leader Winston Churchill.

12:36.160 --> 12:39.920
The Hague Conference resulted in the Council of Europe.

12:39.920 --> 12:46.480
No one can promise in advance what this one would achieve, but we can hope and believe

12:46.480 --> 12:52.240
that it would be the same kind of imaginative step for the good of free men.

12:52.240 --> 12:57.720
As a result of all of these conferences, Colonel JJ Fenns of the Netherlands, the President

12:57.720 --> 13:03.320
of the Parliamentarians, will upon a small group study the report of the so-called

13:03.320 --> 13:09.440
three wise men and see what has happened in recent years since they met and study these

13:09.440 --> 13:12.000
problems of working together.

13:12.000 --> 13:16.600
We know that there have been many instances since then, Suez crisis.

13:16.600 --> 13:23.320
They revolt in Hungary, the Tunisian instance, but showed very well that we sometimes have

13:23.320 --> 13:28.280
little consultation if any at all among our color nations.

13:28.280 --> 13:31.200
I think these things should be avoided.

13:31.200 --> 13:35.360
In all of our studies, we shouldn't lose sight of a really big problem.

13:35.360 --> 13:41.440
That is how to keep a group of free and independent nations working together in time of peace.

13:41.440 --> 13:44.000
In time of war, they eventually unite.

13:44.000 --> 13:49.760
In time of peace, however, when the steps are taken, not which wars are made, they tend

13:49.760 --> 13:50.760
