15:05.560 --> 15:12.360
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, all of us have been concerned about the so-called

15:12.360 --> 15:13.360
recession.

15:13.360 --> 15:18.560
The latest published figures from the Department of Labor show that there are 5,200,000

15:18.560 --> 15:19.560
unemployed.

15:19.560 --> 15:24.960
Reports are that the March figures, when they were available, will show a further increase.

15:24.960 --> 15:29.840
And even these figures do not show the real extent of the cut-in-the-family paycheck.

15:29.840 --> 15:32.400
Over time, it's been largely eliminated everywhere.

15:32.400 --> 15:36.920
And in many instances, work weeks, weeks have been greatly reduced.

15:36.920 --> 15:41.840
Like the other recessions in our history, this one seems to have started on the far and

15:41.840 --> 15:46.240
spread from there to the small towns, the cities, factories, and then to the industrial

15:46.240 --> 15:47.240
areas.

15:47.240 --> 15:52.680
Now, while I do not think it helps matters too much, at all to become hysterical about

15:52.680 --> 15:57.920
the economy, I do think that we ought to do something about it before it gets any worse.

15:57.920 --> 16:00.920
The road program, which the Senate passed this week, will help.

16:00.920 --> 16:05.240
A reduction in prices, which I have been urging, would be a great benefit.

16:05.240 --> 16:09.840
I want to discuss with you another program, which I also think would be a major benefit

16:09.840 --> 16:14.560
to the communities of Tennessee, as well as all other states, and in which I have been

16:14.560 --> 16:16.680
working very hard.

16:16.680 --> 16:21.080
You know there have been many suggestions about accelerating the federal work's program,

16:21.080 --> 16:23.400
the counteracty recession.

16:23.400 --> 16:27.320
The new program that I have been working on in collaboration with Senator Bill Fulbright

16:27.320 --> 16:32.560
of Arkansas, who is chairman of the Senate Banking and Currency Committee, would be

16:32.560 --> 16:39.120
designed to accelerate local public works' programs, not by the old PWA of programs, but

16:39.120 --> 16:43.160
through expanding and liberalizing our existing loan programs.

16:43.160 --> 16:47.480
There is an existence a federal program for assistance to public works planning and

16:47.480 --> 16:48.480
financing.

16:48.480 --> 16:53.400
Its purpose is to provide low interest loans to communities for such work.

16:53.400 --> 16:58.400
Higher rate is snarled up in many restrictions, and as such, isn't really filling the need

16:58.400 --> 16:59.400
that it could.

16:59.400 --> 17:05.240
For all practical purposes, it is now limited to communities of less than 5,000 population

17:05.240 --> 17:08.440
for water and sewer disposal systems.

17:08.440 --> 17:15.840
It provides for interest rates of 4.18% on general obligation bonds, 4.58% on revenue

17:15.840 --> 17:18.720
bonds with 30-year materials.

17:18.720 --> 17:23.360
This makes loans attractive only to the communities with a worse credit rate.

17:23.360 --> 17:27.840
Moreover, this program has only $100 million off the recession.

17:27.840 --> 17:32.880
The bill with Senator Fulbright in our proposing would greatly expand this program.

17:32.880 --> 17:37.600
Instead of just water and sewer systems, we would make eligible public streets, sidewalks,

17:37.600 --> 17:43.320
highways, bridges, parking lots, airports, and other transportation facilities.

17:43.320 --> 17:49.760
Also public recreational facilities, public hospitals, rehabilitation and health centers.

17:49.760 --> 17:53.600
Public and refuge in garbage disposal facilities.

17:53.600 --> 17:56.520
Other public utility facilities.

17:56.520 --> 18:02.200
Public police and fire protection work, public schools, libraries, office and other public

18:02.200 --> 18:05.960
buildings, and public conservation facilities.

18:05.960 --> 18:11.440
We would have the interest rate at a maximum of 1.4% above average rates on all government

18:11.440 --> 18:12.440
debt.

18:12.440 --> 18:18.320
This would result in a present rate of 3% the same as college housing loans.

18:18.320 --> 18:24.000
We think 3% rate for this program would tend to bring down interest rates generally throughout

18:24.000 --> 18:25.720
the economy.

18:25.720 --> 18:30.000
We would increase the authorization from 100 million to 2 billion.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.960
Now, I think the advantages of this program are very great.

18:33.960 --> 18:39.160
First, it would be a much faster one than the public works program, and spurring the economy.

18:39.160 --> 18:44.400
The difficulty with a federal program like the road program is that it's slow and getting

18:44.400 --> 18:45.720
started.

18:45.720 --> 18:47.400
The way has to be appropriated.

18:47.400 --> 18:49.000
Plans have to be drawn.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.840
Lands and right away have to be obtained.

18:51.840 --> 18:57.120
However, since these are all local public works, I have an idea that they could be started

18:57.120 --> 18:58.120
much quicker.

18:58.120 --> 19:03.920
In fact, I think it's quite probable, and I talked with many mayors of Tennessee, and I

19:03.920 --> 19:09.840
know this is true, that there's a large backlog of local projects in virtually every community

19:09.840 --> 19:15.480
in the state of Tennessee as a result of post-lomberment caused by war, inflation, and tight

19:15.480 --> 19:16.480
money.

19:16.480 --> 19:21.120
In order to check my opinion on this, I'm writing, I'm in the process of writing letters to the

19:21.120 --> 19:27.600
mayors of all the cities in Tennessee, a 5,000 population or more, and all the county judges

19:27.600 --> 19:30.200
asking their comments on this program.

19:30.200 --> 19:35.160
I'm also asking them for a list of projects, along with the cost of each, on which they could

19:35.160 --> 19:38.360
speedily go forward if our bill is enacted.

19:38.360 --> 19:41.280
Finally, such a program will not run up a huge federal debt.

19:41.280 --> 19:42.280
The money would be repaid.

19:42.280 --> 19:47.120
The project would be entirely under local direction and with local labor.

19:47.120 --> 19:52.200
I'm most hopeful we can get this bill enacted, and we can get this great boost in our

19:52.200 --> 19:54.200
economy to the people of Tennessee.

19:54.200 --> 20:05.800
Thank you, and goodbyes, until next week.

